Anonymous Sat 17 Apr 2021 03:21:47 No.37964062 Report
Quoted By: >>37964630
Review on EAOS Chap 3+4
I'm just not really a fan of the story man. You have a good eye for detail in a lot of places, the graveyard scene with the plaques comes to mind, but you need to put more of that effort into the dialogue and characters, a lot of the interactions feel weak when they need to be strong.
>Friends don’t let friends stay sad . . .
I get this is a call back to how Anon helped Anne with her family dysfunction but it comes off as tactless because both of them are adults and Anne in particular should know that loss always sticks with you, and it can take a long time to get over the deaths of your parents. That sadness isn't going to just go away. A better line would have been the generic but far more understanding
>I'm here for you.
Or something along that line.
As I read further into this story, I wasn't able to attach myself to this version of Anon and it hurt my immersion. I don't know if other people shared that issue. It's my opinion that this probably would have been told better in first person, with Anon being his OWN character rather than being a self-insert.
The reveal about the Federation being 'evil' was obvious from the beginning.
